    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "so youre saying that prioritizing people's immediate survival is basically just being irresponsible? it feels like you're framing debt reduction as the only \"real\" solution and basically dismissing the argument that social stability is what actually prevents a country from collapsing in the first place. isn't that just a biased way to look at it?",
